FORMER Mamelodi Sundowns midfielder George Lebese and South African television actor Mlungisi Mathe have a striking resemblance. The pair have seen many people draw comparisons in appearance between them in the past. They have even met before and taken a picture together in order to end all the talk about them looking so much alike. Lebese has made a name for himself in the footballing world, playing for some of the biggest clubs in the country. He has represented Kaizer Chiefs, Sundowns and SuperSport United. The 32-year-old has also had a spell in the United States with the Colorado Springs Switchbacks. Mathe, on the other hand, is a famous actor best known for playing the lead role of Emkay Biyela on the SABC soap opera Skeem Saam. He is also a Maskandi artist. 